1. DNS Report
Domain 1: google.com

Command:

dig google.com
Record	Value
A Record	142.250.190.14
TTL	300 seconds
Authoritative Nameservers	ns1.google.com, ns2.google.com, ns3.google.com, ns4.google.com

Why this TTL?

Google changes IP addresses frequently for load balancing and reliability, so a relatively short TTL (300 seconds) allows DNS records to update quickly.

Domain 2: github.com

Command:

dig github.com
Record	Value
A Record	140.82.121.4
TTL	60 seconds
Authoritative Nameservers	dns1.p08.nsone.net, dns2.p08.nsone.net, dns3.p08.nsone.net, dns4.p08.nsone.net

Why this TTL?

GitHub uses a very short TTL to quickly redirect traffic during maintenance or heavy load.

Domain 3: wikipedia.org

