3. Short Written Answer

Website chosen:
https://www.youtube.com

Using the browser's Developer Tools → Network tab, I observed several requests besides the main HTML document:

JavaScript file (.js)
The browser downloaded JavaScript files that provide the website's functionality, including video playback, search, and user interface interactions.
CSS stylesheet (.css)
The browser requested CSS files to control the appearance, layout, fonts, and colors of the website.
Image request (.jpg/.png/.webp)
The browser downloaded images such as the YouTube logo, video thumbnails, and user profile icons to display visual content.

These additional requests are necessary because modern websites consist of many resources besides the main HTML page.
